{
  "name": "sunraga",
  "description": "A santoor shimmering in morning light, struck strings raining bright major sunlight. Struck-string santoor courses, bright and shimmering with fast metallic mallet flutter and many-string resonance — the low course grounds the raga, mid and high courses rain and ornament the melody, a single-string ping glints, top strings cascade in bright droplets, a bowed swell blooms the sympathetic strings into a lush wash, and a rolling tremolo cloud glitters like sun on water. A Lydian @ A=432, additive and clean, radiant and cascading, devotional joy, never heavy, never dreary.",
